Residents of Kiserian, Ongata Rongai and Karen yesterday held demonstrations on Lang&rsquo;ata Road to protest against rogue matatu operators plying the route.They carried banners and tree branches, saying operators are reckless. They accused the National Transport and Safety Authority of being lax in arresting offenders.Kiserian and Ongata Rongai Residents Association chairman Fredrick Gori said , &ldquo;We do not have a problem with matatu operators, but rather how they operate.&rdquo;The residents said operators are allowed to continue working, even after violating traffic rules. They said some of the matatus are owned by influential people &ldquo;so operators cannot be arrested&rdquo;.Kajiado deputy county commissioner Philip Lemalasia assured the residents police will restore order.